Gemini said
*One ID to Track Them All!*

To improve tracking consistency across the platform, we have updated the
primary identifiers used on our dashboard.


In most of the places, different sort of ID=E2=80=99s has been used as the =
primary
tracking identifier. This difference often caused confusion for Admins to
track orders. To eliminate this inconsistency and streamline your
workflow, *Reference
ID* has now been established as the universal primary identifier across
everywhere.


Why We Built This?


We have standardized how orders are identified and displayed across both
the *All Orders* and *Pidge Powered* sections. By making the
*Reference ID* your
main universal anchor, you no longer have to mentally translate between
different IDs when tracking the same order across different tabs.


What=E2=80=99s New!







   1.

   *The New Universal Primary Key:* *Reference ID* is now officially the
   first, fixed, and non-editable column across all *Pidge Powered* pages
   (Overview, Ready to Ship, On Ground, At Warehouse, and Completed).


   2.

   *Clearer Labeling:* We=E2=80=99ve renamed all instances of "Ref ID" and
   "Channel/Ref ID" to a clean, uniform *"Reference ID"* across all
   sub-tabs and the Order Details screen.

   3.

   *Intelligent Date & Time Tracking:*
   -

      *Reference ID* timestamps now reflect the exact *Order Creation* date
      and time with Pidge.
      -

      *Order ID* timestamps will show the *Order Manifestation* date and
      time




What This Means To You








   1.

   *Zero Confusion, Faster Tracking:* No more switching between sections
   and seeing "Ref ID" in one place and "Order ID" in another. A single,
   consistent primary identifier means less cognitive load and faster track=
ing
   for Admins.


   2.

   *Tailored Workspace Control:* By making Order ID optional and giving you
   a standardized starting column, your workspace becomes cleaner, more
   predictable, and easier to scan at a glance.

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
